024/**
025 * A bi-directional mapping of objects to positions in an ordering (which this generates), and vice versa.
026 * Useful for various indirection techniques where you want to be able to retrieve a value in several ways, such as with
027 * multiple Arrangements all sharing the same ordering but with different types for keys.
028 * <br>
029 * Originally, this started as a generic linked hash map with with a fast implementation, originally from fastutil as
030 * Object2IntLinkedOpenHashMap but modified to support indexed access. The code is extremely close to {@link OrderedMap},
031 * and like OrderedMap you can look up keys by index, but this is specialized to int values which it can automatically assign.
032 * <br>
033 * <p>Instances of this class use a hash table to represent a map. The table is filled up to a specified <em>load factor</em>, and then doubled in size to accommodate new entries. If the table is
034 * emptied below <em>one fourth</em> of the load factor, it is halved in size. However, halving is not performed when deleting entries from an iterator, as it would interfere with the iteration
035 * process.
036 * </p>
037 * <p>Note that {@link #clear()} does not modify the hash table size. Rather, a family of {@linkplain #trim() trimming methods} lets you control the size of the table; this is particularly useful if
038 * you reuse instances of this class.
039 * </p>
040 * <p>Iterators generated by this map will enumerate pairs in the same order in which they have been added to the map (addition of pairs whose key is already present in the set does not change the
041 * iteration order). Note that this order has nothing in common with the natural order of the keys. The order is kept by means of a int-specialized list, {@link IntVLA}, and is modifiable with this
042 * class' {@link #reorder(int...)} and {@link #shuffle(IRNG)} methods, among other tools.
043 * </p>
044 * <p>This class implements the interface of a sorted map, so to allow easy access of the iteration order: for instance, you can get the first key in iteration order with {@code firstKey()} without
045 * having to create an iterator; however, this class partially violates the {@link SortedMap} contract because all submap methods throw an exception and {@link #comparator()} returns always
046 * <code>null</code>.
047 * </p>
048 * <p>
049 * Additional methods, such as <code>getAndMoveToFirst()</code>, make it easy to use instances of this class as a cache (e.g., with LRU policy).
050 * </p>
051 * <br>
052 * Thank you, Sebastiano Vigna, for making FastUtil available to the public with such high quality.
053 * <br>
054 * See https://github.com/vigna/fastutil for the original library.
055 *
056 * @author Sebastiano Vigna (responsible for all the hard parts)
057 * @author Tommy Ettinger (mostly responsible for squashing several layers of parent classes into one monster class)
058 */
059public class Arrangement<K> implements SortedMap<K, Integer>, Iterable<K>, Serializable, Cloneable {

135    /**
136     * Creates a new Arrangement.
137     * <p>
138     * <p>The actual table size will be the least power of two greater than <code>expected</code>/<code>f</code>.
139     *
140     * @param expected the expected number of elements in the hash set.
141     * @param f        the load factor.

144    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
145    public Arrangement(final int expected, final float f) {
146        if (f <= 0 || f > 1)
147            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Load factor must be greater than 0 and smaller than or equal to 1");
148        if (expected < 0) throw new IllegalArgumentException("The expected number of elements must be nonnegative");
149        this.f = f;
150        n = arraySize(expected, f);
151        mask = n - 1;
152        maxFill = maxFill(n, f);
153        key = (K[]) new Object[n + 1];
154        value = new int[n + 1];
155        //link = new long[n + 1];
156        order = new IntVLA(expected);
157        hasher = CrossHash.mildHasher;
158    }

341    private int realSize() {
342        return containsNullKey ? size - 1 : size;
343    }
344    private void ensureCapacity(final int capacity) {
345        final int needed = arraySize(capacity, f);
346        if (needed > n)
347            rehash(needed);
348    }
349    private void tryCapacity(final long capacity) {
350        final int needed = (int) Math.min(
351                1 << 30,
352                Math.max(2, HashCommon.nextPowerOfTwo((long) Math.ceil(capacity
353                        / f))));
354        if (needed > n)
355            rehash(needed);
356    }
357    private int removeEntry(final int pos) {
358        size--;
359        fixOrder(pos);
360        shiftKeys(pos);
361        final int oldValue = value[pos];
362        fixValues(oldValue);
363        if (size < (maxFill >>> 2) && n > DEFAULT_INITIAL_SIZE)
364            rehash(n / 2);
365        return oldValue;
366    }
367    private int removeNullEntry() {
368        containsNullKey = false;
369        key[n] = null;
370        final int oldValue = value[n];
371        size--;
372        fixOrder(n);
373        fixValues(oldValue);
374        if (size < (maxFill >>> 2) && n > DEFAULT_INITIAL_SIZE)
375            rehash(n / 2);
376        return oldValue;
377    }

379    @Override
380    public void putAll(Map<? extends K, ? extends Integer> m) {
381        if (f <= .5)
382            ensureCapacity(m.size()); // The resulting map will be sized for
383            // m.size() elements
384        else
385            tryCapacity(size() + m.size()); // The resulting map will be
386        int n = m.size();
387        final Iterator<? extends K> i = m
388                .keySet().iterator();
389        while (n-- != 0) {
390            add(i.next());
391        }
392    }

394    public void putAll(K[] keyArray) {
395        int n = keyArray.length;
396        if (f <= .5)
397            ensureCapacity(n); // The resulting map will be sized for
398            // m.size() elements
399        else
400            tryCapacity(size() + n); // The resulting map will be
401        // tentatively sized for size() + keyArray.length elements
402        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
403            add(keyArray[i]);
404        }
405    }

408        if (f <= .5)
409            ensureCapacity(keyColl.size()); // The resulting map will be sized for

412            tryCapacity(size() + keyColl.size()); // The resulting map will be

416            add(it.next());

419    private int insert(final K k) {
420        int pos;
421        if (k == null) {
422            if (containsNullKey)
423                return n;
424            containsNullKey = true;
425            pos = n;
426        } else {
427            K curr;
428            final K[] key = this.key;
429            // The starting point.
430            if ((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask]) != null) {
431                if (hasher.areEqual(curr, k)) {
432                    return pos;
433                }
434                while ((curr = key[pos = (pos + 1) & mask]) != null)
435                    if (hasher.areEqual(curr, k)) {
436                        return pos;
437                    }
438            }
439        }
440        key[pos] = k;
441        order.add(pos);
442        value[pos] = size;
443        if (size++ >= maxFill)
444            rehash(arraySize(size + 1, f));
445        return -1;
446    }
447    private int insertAt(final K k, final int at) {
448        int pos;
449        if (k == null) {
450            if (containsNullKey)
451                return n;
452            containsNullKey = true;
453            pos = n;
454        } else {
455            K curr;
456            final K[] key = this.key;
457            // The starting point.
458            if ((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask]) != null) {
459                if (hasher.areEqual(curr, k)) {
460                    order.removeIndex(value[pos]);
461                    order.insert(at, pos);
462                    return pos;
463                }
464                while ((curr = key[pos = (pos + 1) & mask]) != null)
465                    if (hasher.areEqual(curr, k)) {
466                        order.removeIndex(value[pos]);
467                        order.insert(at, pos);
468                        return pos;
469                    }
470            }
471        }
472        key[pos] = k;
473        order.insert(at, pos);
474        value[pos] = at;
475        if (size++ >= maxFill)
476            rehash(arraySize(size + 1, f));
477        return pos;
478    }

540    protected void fixValues(int start)
541    {
542        for (int i = start; i < size; i++) {
543            value[order.items[i]] = i;
544        }
545    }

547    /**
548     * Shifts left entries with the specified hash code, starting at the
549     * specified position, and empties the resulting free entry.
550     *
551     * @param pos
552     *            a starting position.
553     */
554    protected final void shiftKeys(int pos) {
555        // Shift entries with the same hash.
556        int last, slot;
557        K curr;
558        final K[] key = this.key;
559        for (;;) {
560            pos = ((last = pos) + 1) & mask;
561            for (;;) {
562                if ((curr = key[pos]) == null) {
563                    key[last] = null;
564                    return;
565                }
566                slot = (hasher.hash(curr))
567                        & mask;
568                if (last <= pos ? last >= slot || slot > pos : last >= slot
569                        && slot > pos)
570                    break;
571                pos = (pos + 1) & mask;
572            }
573            key[last] = curr;
574            fixOrder(pos, last);
575        }
576    }
577
578    /**
579     * Shifts left entries with the specified hash code, starting at the
580     * specified position, and empties the resulting free entry.
581     *
582     * @param pos
583     *            a starting position.
584     */
585    protected final void shiftKeysValues(int pos) {
586        // Shift entries with the same hash.
587        int last, slot;
588        K curr;
589        int v;
590        final K[] key = this.key;
591        final int[] val = this.value;
592        for (;;) {
593            pos = ((last = pos) + 1) & mask;
594            for (;;) {
595                if ((curr = key[pos]) == null) {
596                    key[last] = null;
597                    val[last] = -1;
598                    return;
599                }
600                v = val[pos];
601                slot = (hasher.hash(curr))
602                        & mask;
603                if (last <= pos ? last >= slot || slot > pos : last >= slot
604                        && slot > pos)
605                    break;
606                pos = (pos + 1) & mask;
607            }
608            key[last] = curr;
609            val[last] = v;
610            fixOrder(pos, last);
611        }
612    }
613    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
614    protected Integer rem(final Object k) {
615        if (k == null) {
616            if (containsNullKey)
617                return removeNullEntry();
618            return null;
619        }
620        K curr;
621        final K[] key = this.key;
622        int pos;
623        // The starting point.
624        if ((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask]) == null)
625            return null;
626        if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
627            return removeEntry(pos);
628        while (true) {
629            if ((curr = key[pos = (pos + 1) & mask]) == null)
630                return null;
631            if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
632                return removeEntry(pos);
633        }
634    }
635    public Integer remove(Object o)
636    {
637        return rem(o);
638    }
639    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
640    public int removeInt(final Object k) {
641        if (k == null) {
642            if (containsNullKey)
643                return removeNullEntry();
644            return defRetValue;
645        }
646        K curr;
647        final K[] key = this.key;
648        int pos;
649        // The starting point.
650        if ((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask]) == null)
651            return defRetValue;
652        if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
653            return removeEntry(pos);
654        while (true) {
655            if ((curr = key[pos = (pos + 1) & mask]) == null)
656                return defRetValue;
657            if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
658                return removeEntry(pos);
659        }
660    }
661    private int setValue(final int pos, final int v) {
662        final int oldValue = value[pos];
663        value[pos] = v;
664        return oldValue;
665    }
666    /**
667     * Removes the mapping associated with the first key in iteration order.
668     *
669     * @return the value previously associated with the first key in iteration
670     *         order.
671     * @throws NoSuchElementException
672     *             is this map is empty.
673     */
674    public K removeFirst() {
675        if (size == 0)
676            throw new NoSuchElementException();
677        final int pos = order.removeIndex(0);
678        K fst = key[pos];
679        size--;
680        final int v = value[pos];
681        if (pos == n) {
682            containsNullKey = false;
683            key[n] = null;
684        } else
685            shiftKeys(pos);
686        fixValues(v);
687        if (size < maxFill / 4 && n > DEFAULT_INITIAL_SIZE)
688            rehash(n / 2);
689        return fst;
690    }
691    /**
692     * Removes the mapping associated with the last key in iteration order.
693     *
694     * @return the value previously associated with the last key in iteration
695     *         order.
696     * @throws NoSuchElementException
697     *             is this map is empty.
698     */
699    public K removeLast() {
700        if (size == 0)
701            throw new NoSuchElementException();
702        final int pos = order.pop();
703        K lst = key[pos];
704        size--;
705        if (pos == n) {
706            containsNullKey = false;
707            key[n] = null;
708        } else
709            shiftKeys(pos);
710        //fixValues(v); // one case where we don't need to do this; the last item is just given -1
711        value[pos] = -1;
712        if (size < maxFill >> 2 && n > DEFAULT_INITIAL_SIZE)
713            rehash(n >> 1);
714        return lst;
715    }
716    private void moveIndexToFirst(final int i) {
717        if(size <= 1 || order.items[0] == i)
718            return;
719        order.moveToFirst(i);
720        fixValues(0);
721    }
722    private void moveIndexToLast(final int i) {
723        if(size <= 1 || order.items[order.size-1] == i)
724            return;
725        order.moveToLast(i);
726        fixValues(i);
727    }
728    /**
729     * Returns the value to which the given key is mapped; if the key is
730     * present, it is moved to the first position of the iteration order.
731     *
732     * @param k
733     *            the key.
734     * @return the corresponding value, or -1 if no value was present for the given key.
735     */
736    public int getAndMoveToFirst(final K k) {
737        if (k == null) {
738            if (containsNullKey) {
739                moveIndexToFirst(n);
740                return value[n];
741            }
742            return defRetValue;
743        }
744        K curr;
745        final K[] key = this.key;
746        int pos;
747        // The starting point.
748        if ((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask]) == null)
749            return defRetValue;
750        if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr)) {
751            moveIndexToFirst(pos);
752            return value[pos];
753        }
754        // There's always an unused entry.
755        while (true) {
756            if ((curr = key[pos = (pos + 1) & mask]) == null)
757                return defRetValue;
758            if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr)) {
759                moveIndexToFirst(pos);
760                return value[pos];
761            }
762        }
763    }

800    /**
801     * Adds a pair to the map; if the key is already present, it is moved to the
802     * first position of the iteration order.
803     *
804     * @param k
805     *            the key.
806     * @param v
807     *            the value.
808     * @return the old value, or -1 if no value was present for the given key.
809     */
810    public int putAndMoveToFirst(final K k, final int v) {
811        int pos;
812        if (k == null) {
813            if (containsNullKey) {
814                moveIndexToFirst(n);
815                return setValue(n, 0);
816            }
817            containsNullKey = true;
818            pos = n;
819        } else {
820            K curr;
821            final K[] key = this.key;
822            // The starting point.
823            if (!((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask]) == null)) {
824                if (hasher.areEqual(curr, k)) {
825                    moveIndexToFirst(pos);
826                    return setValue(pos, 0);
827                }
828                while (!((curr = key[pos = (pos + 1) & mask]) == null))
829                    if (hasher.areEqual(curr, k)) {
830                        moveIndexToFirst(pos);
831                        return setValue(pos, 0);
832                    }
833            }
834        }
835        key[pos] = k;
836        order.insert(0, pos);
837        fixValues(0);
838        if (size++ >= maxFill)
839            rehash(arraySize(size, f));
840        return defRetValue;
841    }

856                moveIndexToLast(n);
857                return setValue(n, size - 1);

1060     * This method will complete in logarithmic time or better.
1061     *
1062     * @param s the source position.
1063     * @param d the destination position.

1065    protected void fixOrder(int s, int d) {
1066        if(size == 0)
1067            return;
1068        if (size == 1 || order.items[0] == s) {
1069            order.set(0, d);
1070        }
1071        else if (order.items[order.size-1] == s) {
1072            order.set(order.size - 1, d);
1073        }
1074        else
1075        {
1076            int idx = order.indexOf(s);
1077            order.set(idx, d);
1078        }

1414            final K[] key = Arrangement.this.key;
1415            int pos;
1416            // The starting point.
1417            if ((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask]) == null)
1418                return false;
1419            if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
1420                return value[pos] == v;
1421            // There's always an unused entry.
1422            while (true) {
1423                if ((curr = key[pos = (pos + 1) & mask]) == null)
1424                    return false;
1425                if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
1426                    return value[pos] == v;
1427            }
1428        }
1429        @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
1430        protected boolean rem(final Object o) {
1431            if (!(o instanceof Map.Entry))
1432                return false;
1433            final Entry<?, ?> e = (Entry<?, ?>) o;
1434            final K k = (K) e.getKey();
1435            final int v = (Integer) e.getValue();
1436            if (k == null) {
1437                if (containsNullKey
1438                        && value[n] == v) {
1439                    removeNullEntry();
1440                    return true;
1441                }
1442                return false;
1443            }
1444            K curr;
1445            final K[] key = Arrangement.this.key;
1446            int pos;
1447            // The starting point.
1448            if ((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask]) == null)
1449                return false;
1450            if (hasher.areEqual(curr, k)) {
1451                if (value[pos] == v) {
1452                    removeEntry(pos);
1453                    return true;
1454                }
1455                return false;
1456            }
1457            while (true) {
1458                if ((curr = key[pos = (pos + 1) & mask]) == null)
1459                    return false;
1460                if (hasher.areEqual(curr, k)) {
1461                    if (value[pos] == v) {
1462                        removeEntry(pos);
1463                        return true;
1464                    }
1465                }
1466            }
1467        }

1470        {
1471            return rem(o);

1937     * Rehashes this map if the table is too large.
1938     * <p>
1939     * <P>Let <var>N</var> be the smallest table size that can hold <code>max(n,{@link #size()})</code> entries, still satisfying the load factor. If the current table size is smaller than or equal to
1940     * <var>N</var>, this method does nothing. Otherwise, it rehashes this map in a table of size <var>N</var>.
1941     * <p>
1942     * <P>This method is useful when reusing maps. {@linkplain #clear() Clearing a map} leaves the table size untouched. If you are reusing a map many times, you can call this method with a typical
1943     * size to avoid keeping around a very large table just because of a few large transient maps.

1947     * @see #trim()

1954        } catch (Exception cantDoIt) {
1955            return false;
1956        }

1960    /**
1961     * Rehashes the map.
1962     *
1963     * <P>
1964     * This method implements the basic rehashing strategy, and may be overriden
1965     * by subclasses implementing different rehashing strategies (e.g.,
1966     * disk-based rehashing). However, you should not override this method
1967     * unless you understand the internal workings of this class.
1968     *
1969     * @param newN
1970     *            the new size
1971     */
1972
1973    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
1974    protected void rehash(final int newN) {
1975        final K[] key = this.key;
1976        final int[] value = this.value;
1977        final int mask = newN - 1; // Note that this is used by the hashing macro
1978        final K[] newKey = (K[]) new Object[newN + 1];
1979        final int[] newValue = new int[newN + 1];
1980        final int sz = order.size;
1981        K k;
1982        int i, pos;
1983        final int[] oi = order.items;
1984        for (int q = 0; q < sz; q++) {
1985            i = oi[q];
1986            if ((k = key[i]) == null)
1987                pos = newN;
1988            else {
1989                pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask;
1990                while (newKey[pos] != null)
1991                    pos = (pos + 1) & mask;
1992            }
1993            newKey[pos] = k;
1994            newValue[pos] = value[i];
1995            oi[q] = pos;
1996        }
1997
1998        n = newN;
1999        this.mask = mask;
2000        maxFill = maxFill(n, f);
2001        this.key = newKey;
2002        this.value = newValue;
2003    }

2006     *

2009     * map, however, is not cloned. Note that this makes a difference only for
2010     * object keys.
2011     *

2014    @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
2015    @GwtIncompatible
2016    public Arrangement<K> clone() {
2017        Arrangement<K> c;

2021            System.arraycopy(key, 0, c.key, 0, n + 1);

2031    /**
2032     * Returns a hash code for this map.
2033     *
2034     * This method overrides the generic method provided by the superclass.
2035     * Since <code>equals()</code> is not overriden, it is important that the
2036     * value returned by this method is the same value as the one returned by
2037     * the overriden method.
2038     *
2039     * @return a hash code for this map.
2040     */
2041    public int hashCode() {
2042        int h = 0;
2043        for (int j = realSize(), i = 0, t = 0; j-- != 0;) {
2044            while (key[i] == null)
2045                i++;
2046            if (this != key[i])
2047                t = hasher.hash(key[i]);
2048            t ^= value[i];
2049            h += t;
2050            i++;
2051        }
2052        // Zero / null keys have hash zero.
2053        if (containsNullKey)
2054            h += value[n];
2055        return h;
2056    }

2106     * <P>This method iterates over the given type-specific iterator and stores the elements returned, up to a maximum of <code>length</code>, in the given array starting at <code>offset</code>. The
2107     * number of actually unwrapped elements is returned (it may be less than <code>max</code> if the iterator emits less than <code>max</code> elements).
2108     *
2109     * @param i      a type-specific iterator.
2110     * @param array  an array to contain the output of the iterator.
2111     * @param offset the first element of the array to be returned.
2112     * @param max    the maximum number of elements to unwrap.
2113     * @return the number of elements unwrapped.
2114     */
2115    private int unwrap(final ValueIterator i, final Object[] array, int offset, final int max) {
2116        if (max < 0) throw new IllegalArgumentException("The maximum number of elements (" + max + ") is negative");
2117        if (offset < 0 || offset + max > array.length) throw new IllegalArgumentException();
2118        int j = max;
2119        while (j-- != 0 && i.hasNext())
2120            array[offset++] = i.next();
2121        return max - j - 1;
2122    }

2390    private int alterEntry(final int pos, final K replacement) {
2391        final int[] value = this.value;
2392        final int v = value[pos], op = order.indexOf(pos);
2393        shiftKeysValues(pos);
2394
2395        int rep;
2396        if (replacement == null) {
2397            if (containsNullKey)
2398                return v;
2399            rep = n;
2400            containsNullKey = true;
2401        } else {
2402            K curr;
2403            final K[] key = this.key;
2404
2405            // The starting point.
2406            if (!((curr = key[rep = (hasher.hash(replacement)) & mask]) == null)) {
2407                if (hasher.areEqual(curr, replacement))
2408                    return v;
2409                while (!((curr = key[rep = (rep + 1) & mask]) == null))
2410                    if (hasher.areEqual(curr, replacement))
2411                        return v;
2412            }
2413            key[rep] = replacement;
2414            value[rep] = v;
2415        }
2416        order.set(op, rep);
2417        return v;
2418    }

2448    /**
2449     * Swaps a key, original, for another key, replacement, while keeping replacement at the same point in the iteration
2450     * order as original and keeping it associated with the same value (which also keeps its iteration index).
2451     * @param original the key to find and swap out
2452     * @param replacement the key to replace original with
2453     * @return the value associated with original before, and replacement now
2454     */
2455    public int alter(final K original, final K replacement) {
2456        if (original == null) {
2457            if (containsNullKey) {
2458                return alterNullEntry(replacement);
2459            }
2460            else
2461                return add(replacement);
2462        }
2463        else if(hasher.areEqual(original, replacement))
2464            return getInt(original);
2465        K curr;
2466        final K[] key = this.key;
2467        int pos;
2468        // The starting point.
2469        if ((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(original)) & mask]) == null)
2470            return add(replacement);
2471        if (hasher.areEqual(original, curr))
2472            return alterEntry(pos, replacement);
2473        while (true) {
2474            if ((curr = key[pos = (pos + 1) & mask]) == null)
2475                return add(replacement);
2476            if (hasher.areEqual(original, curr))
2477                return alterEntry(pos, replacement);
2478        }
2479    }

2556    protected int positionOf(final Object k) {
2557        if (k == null)
2558        {
2559            return (containsNullKey) ? n : -1;
2560        }
2561        K curr;
2562        final K[] key = this.key;
2563        int pos;
2564        // The starting point.
2565        if ((curr = key[pos = (hasher.hash(k)) & mask]) == null)
2566            return -1;

2568            return pos;

2570        while (true) {

2572                return -1;
2573            if (hasher.areEqual(k, curr))
2574                return pos;

2581     * present, or because left and right are the same reference (so swapping would do nothing)).

2587    {

2590        if(l < 0) return false;

2592        if(r < 0) return false;
